tree.regenerate_confirm:
Please use this function only outside of the working hours, e.g. at the weekend or in the evening, because the system can only be used with restrictions due to high load!

With Start, the Doc Cirrus rules for EBM and GOÄ are executed again. The results of the Doc Cirrus rules that were previously in the system are discarded (depending on the selection, see below: "Erase error log"). Thereafter, the rules will be re-applied depending on the selection of "Entry Types" and "Case Folders" for the patient entries of the selected period. This action lasts the longer the later you are in the selected period, e.g. a quarter, that means the more notes, diagnoses and services have already been documented.

showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_INTRO: A user can be assigned in one or more authorization groups. The groups are linked to the following rights in the system:
showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_REDUCED_USER_TEXT: Can edit appointments, patients and medical documentation (does not see any services and invoices). Does not have access to the system from the outside depending on the configuration.
showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_USER_TEXT: Can process appointments, patients and services. Does not have access to the system from the outside depending on the configuration.
showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_SUPERUSER_TEXT: An Employee who can additionally configure the system professionally and prepare the invoicing (release activities in the case file, carry out preliminary check, correct errors). Always has access from the outside to the system.
showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_PHYSICIAN_TEXT: An Employee+ of the additional file entries can release and cancel. Always has access from the outside to the system.
showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_CONTROLLER_TEXT: An Employee+ who can additionally release and cancel all physicians, finally executes all billing types and can view all licensed reports and evaluations. Always has access from the outside to the system.
showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_ADMIN_TEXT: Has all rights in the system except the right to delete its own access or to remove itself from the group of administrators (for another administrator, however, it can do it). Always has access from the outside to the system.
showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_SUPPORT_TEXT: A support administrator who has the right to change the status of activities. All activities in the case file which have a status that can not be changed are to be put back into the status valid. Please note that you can use entries that contain, for example, already settled, the status can be set off again and thus, if necessary, recalculated already billed services. All activities of this user are recorded in the Auditlog for the purpose of full traceability.
showIdentityInfoDialog.INFO_ENDING: Please note that a employee of the type physician is automatically assigned to the physicians authorization group. Otherwise, all combinations can be set in your practice.

showRoleInfoDialog.INFO_TEXT: The function role is necessary for the distribution and visibility of tasks in the task system. You can specifically assign people to groups in groups. This also includes the visibility of the tasks in the task list. For example, if an employee is entered in the addressed role, the employee can see and edit the task. If the employee is not registered, he does not see the tasks displayed in his task overview. The assignment of employees to roles and the creation of new roles takes place in the employee configuration.

text.TYPES_DESCRIPTION:
Consultation
is a normal presence of a patient in a doctor's office.

Online consultation
For this appointment, the patient receives an e-mail with instructions for the expiration, usage conditions and the access link 30 minutes before the appointment. Through this link, the patient can then enter the online consultation room. The practice receives at the same time a task (role reception), with a link to the patient's file and a link which allows the patient to enter the online consultation room of this patient. The reception takes over the task, greets the patient in the online consultation room, then leaves it again and then addresses the task to the doctor, who carries out the consultation. The physician takes over the task, enters the consultation room at the time of the appointment, documents normal in the patient's file, and sets the task to be completed after the appointment.

Online Conference
e.g. for scheduled online consoles or tumor conferences. Several participants (with inSuite account or without) as well as the patients to be discussed can be defined. The participants and the practice (roll reception) receive a due task 30 minutes before the appointment in each case with an access link to the conference room and the links to the patient records. External participants receive an e-mail with instructions on the expiry of the usage requirements and the access link with access link to the conference room. In the online conference room, the names of the patients to be discussed are listed (surname, first name, DD.MM.YYYY). The recordings during the meeting are then made by the participants with the respective patient name.

Terms of use

Basic service inSuite: {moduleName}

Dear inSuite users,

{moduleName} Is not part of your use and service scope of the InSuite and offers you e.g. the following options:

INTIME: Appointment booking on the practice website and internally in a central calendar system
Intelligent assignment of appointment for optimum utilization without waiting time
Less no-show patients through integrated reminder service
No waiting room commitment through real-time information on waiting times for patients and staff
INFORM: Everyday comfortable Paperless practice -> No additional software required to edit, everything integrated
Include forms in treatment processes -> No media breaks, no duplication
Numerous templates for each case -> doctor's letter, recipes, notes, transfers, etc.
Intuitive design of forms -> Export and printing is always simple and versatile
Automatic transfer of patient data -> Securely use already collected data
Interactive and individual history forms -> Add external documents (pictures etc.)
Economically well equipped -> Costs, reminders, personal accounts, etc.
INVOICE: Revision-proof with KBV certification for GKV -> EBM, GebüH, GOÄ, UVGOÄ and Co. - all here
Create billing directly from the inSuite -> 1-Click billing and shipping via KV-Connect
Central billing of several workplaces -> Management of several units and doctors bundle
Automatic validation and completion -> All budgets and test times always under control
Create your own invoices and receipts -> Design and use comfortable templates
Automated generation of invoices -> incoming payments, reminder, quotation
With all auxiliary services comfortable working -> account book, PVS interface and much more
INPORT: All devices are optimally integrated -> Simply connect medical devices, printers and co.
Setting up and configuring printers -> Special configuration for forms, formats, printing boxes, etc.
Fast and secure logging in and out using personalized cards
Device integration using device servers on workstation computers and servers
Modeling and configuring interfaces for devices and third-party software (GDT, HL7, DICOM, XML ...)
INSIGHT: Use the data in your inSuite for sustainable improvements.
InSight provides key figures and business evaluations in real-time.
Use inSight to create your own evaluations and statistics.
This allows you to find specific sources of error, optimize revenues, identify inter-relationships.

Welcome $fullname$.

Your registration in the Health Portal was successful.

To activate your customer account, you have to confirm your email address. Please click on the following button and log in with your access data.

Confirm email address

If you do not see a button, you can also copy the following URL into the address field of your web browser:
$optin$


After activating your account, the entire range of functions of the health portal is available. So you can e.g. make an appointment with your practice:
  • Select the attending doctor from the opening times. Then click on the "Appointment" button.
  • Select the desired date and, if necessary, the type of appointment.
  • There are three dates to choose from. When you have made a selection, click on "Book".
  • You can send your practice more information in the "Booking information" field.
  • After clicking on "Book", you have now made a binding appointment with your practice.

Best regards,
Your Health Portal, powered by Doc Cirrus

changePassword.GUIDELINES:
KV-Connect Passwörter müssen den folgenden Anforderungen genügen:

  • mindestens 8 Zeichen lang
    Je länger, desto sicherer; max. 200 Zeichen möglich.
  • mindestens zwei Großbuchstaben enthalten
    Als Großbuchstaben zählen die Zeichen A - Z; nicht dazu gehören Ä, Ö, Ü.
  • mindestens zwei Kleinbuchstaben enthalten
    Als Kleinbuchstaben zählen die Zeichen a - z; nicht dazu gehören ä, ö, ü,ß.
  • mindestens eine Ziffer enthalten.

Sonderzeichen ( z.B. !$%&()=?+#*~-_.,;<>|@^{[]} ), ä, Ä, ö, Ö, ü, Ü und ß sowie das Leerzeichen sind ebenfalls erlaubt.Ihre Verwendung erschwert das Erraten des Kennwortes.

Die Einhaltung dieser Anforderungen sowie die Änderung des Initialpasswortes werden systemseitig erzwungen.

Tipp: Ein "gutes" Passwort erhalten Sie in der Regel, wenn Sie die Anfangsbuchstaben der Wörter einesSatzes, den Sie sich leicht merken können, zu einem Passwort zusammensetzen.
Beispiel: "Meine(!) Patienten sind vom 1. Juli an kerngesund" wird zum Passwort "M(!)Psv1.Jak".

Beachten Sie zudem folgende Regelungen des BSI:

  • Das Passwort muss regelmäßig gewechselt werden, z.B. alle 90 Tage.
  • Ein Passwortwechsel ist durchzuführen, wenn das Passwort unautorisierten Personen bekannt geworden ist oder der Verdacht besteht.
  • Alte Passwörter sollten nach einem Passwortwechsel nicht mehr verwendet werden.
